1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:02,033
<b>You've probably heard it a million times.</b>

2
00:00:02,733 --> 00:00:05,033
<b>Sykes-Picot drew the Middle East borders.</b>

3
00:00:06,133 --> 00:00:07,333
<b>ISIS cited it when they</b>

4
00:00:07,333 --> 00:00:09,266
<b>bulldozed the Iraq-Syria border.</b>

5
00:00:10,066 --> 00:00:10,666
<b>Kurdish independence</b>

6
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:12,533
<b>advocates point to it.</b>

7
00:00:12,966 --> 00:00:14,033
<b>Analysts on Palestine</b>

8
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,033
<b>bring it up constantly.</b>

9
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:17,933
<b>And politicians love to say Britain and</b>

10
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:19,266
<b>France carved up the</b>

11
00:00:19,266 --> 00:00:20,266
<b>Middle East with a ruler.</b>

12
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:22,766
<b>But guess what? They're all wrong.</b>

13
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,933
<b>I went through the original documents.</b>

14
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,699
<b>The actual Sykes-Picot text, the</b>

15
00:00:27,699 --> 00:00:29,233
<b>Hussein-McMahon letters,</b>

16
00:00:29,866 --> 00:00:31,266
<b>San Remo Records and</b>

17
00:00:31,266 --> 00:00:32,533
<b>League of Nations archives.</b>

18
00:00:32,966 --> 00:00:34,666
<b>And what I found, it's</b>

19
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:35,666
<b>not what we've been told.</b>

20
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:37,233
<b>Let's break it down.</b>

21
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:39,233
<b>People say this 1916</b>

22
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:40,566
