<b>Syria-Palestine 1923.</b>

34
00:01:09,599 --> 00:01:11,533
<b>Transjordan 1921.</b>

35
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:13,733
<b>Not 1916.</b>

36
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:16,666
<b>We're talking 10 to 15 years later.</b>

37
00:01:17,633 --> 00:01:18,866
<b>And here's why that matters.</b>

38
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:22,466
<b>When we blame everything on one 1916 map,</b>

39
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:24,300
<b>we miss the actual story.</b>

40
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:26,766
<b>The decade of broken promises.</b>

41
00:01:27,266 --> 00:01:28,433
<b>The oil deals.</b>

42
00:01:28,966 --> 00:01:31,333
<b>The local resistance that changed things.</b>

43
00:01:31,766 --> 00:01:32,900
<b>All of it gets erased.</b>

44
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,333
<b>Because here's what people forget.</b>

45
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:37,800
<b>These places already existed.</b>

46
00:01:38,566 --> 00:01:40,633
<b>Look at this Ottoman map from 1893.</b>

47
00:01:41,666 --> 00:01:42,466
<b>Three provinces.</b>

48
00:01:43,366 --> 00:01:45,133
<b>Basra, Baghdad and Mosul.</b>

49
00:01:45,766 --> 00:01:46,666
<b>And across them the</b>

50
00:01:46,666 --> 00:01:48,766
<b>label, Al-Iraq Al Arabi.</b>

51
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:49,966
<b>Arab-Iraq.</b>

52
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,966
<b>Iraq wasn't invented by Europeans.</b>

53
00:01:53,566 --> 00:01:54,433
<b>Neither was Syria.</b>

54
00:01:55,133 --> 00:01:56,866
<b>These lined up with Ottoman provinces</b>

55
00:01:56,866 --> 00:01:59,366
<b>like Damascus, Aleppo and Beirut.</b>

56
00:02:00,566 --> 00:02:02,566
<b>So when Europeans showed up, they weren't</b>

57
00:02:02,566 --> 00:02:04,099
<b>drawing on a blank map.</b>

58
00:02:04,566 --> 00:02:07,133
<b>They were redrawing someone else's.</b>

59
00:02:07,666 --> 00:02:09,433
<b>And that's where the real problem starts.</b>

60
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:10,866
<b>Because Britain didn't</b>

61
00:02:10,866 --> 00:02:12,366
<b>just draw bad borders.</b>

62
00:02:12,733 --> 00:02:13,633
<b>They made three</b>

63
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:15,533
<b>completely contradictory promises</b>

64
00:02:15,666 --> 00:02:16,599
<b>to three different</b>

65
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:18,266
<b>groups about the same land.</b>

66
00:02:19,466 --> 00:02:21,166
<b>July 14, 1915.</b>

67
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,633
<b>Sharif Hussein of Mecca writes to Britain</b>

68
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:27,133
<b>demanding a massive Arab kingdom.</b>

69
00:02:28,133 --> 00:02:31,166
<b>Syria, Iraq, Arabia and even Palestine.</b>

70
00:02:32,066 --> 00:02:35,333
<b>On October 24, 1915, the British High</b>

71
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:37,533
<b>Commissioner Henry McMahon replies.</b>

72
00:02:38,166 --> 00:02:40,466
<b>And I'm quoting directly here.</b>

73
00:02:40,866 --> 00:02:42,833
<b>"Subject to the above modifications,</b>

74
00:02:43,433 --> 00:02:44,599
<b>Great Britain is prepared</b>

75
00:02:44,599 --> 00:02:46,300
<b>to recognize and support</b>

76
